Sometimes, you want a type, not just an underlying `bool` value. Simple example is provided by the tag dispatch technique:

```
void foo(std::true_type)  { ... }
void foo(std::false_type) { ... }

foo(std::is_same&lt;T, S&gt;{});
```

If `std::is_same` were just a `bool` variable template, this code would not be that elegant.

